2. The cosine similarity-based robustness metric $\mathcal{R}_{cs}$ is defined as:
   $$
   \mathcal{R}_{cs}(f, x, P, K) = 1 - \min_{k_1,k_2 \in K} \cos(f(P(x, k_1)), f(P(x, k_2))) \cdot \frac{1}{2}
   $$
