When the predicted mask is a perfect subset of the ground-truth mask, the intersection equals the predicted mask, and the union equals the ground-truth mask. In this case, the IoU becomes 1.0, indicating perfect overlap. This implies that the IoU metric is highly sensitive to false positives because any addition of pixels outside the ground-truth mask (false positives) would increase the union while keeping the intersection constant, thereby decreasing the IoU value.

